The paper proposes a new metric for measuring the impact of publications on Twitter, which falls under the category of social media analysis. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper also involves data analysis and information retrieval, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of publications on Twitter, which could also fall under cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks).
